    "notes": [
      "Three-player JS oracle canary for active PrintManager.stop side effects during death.",
      "p0 starts printing with an active PrintManager, crosses the normal right wall, and dies while p1 and p2 survive so the round does not end.",
      "Avatar.die emits the normal non-important death point before PrintManager.stop emits the important stop point and printing=false property.",
      "PrintManager.test does not run after death; stop clears active, distance, lastX, and lastY instead of updating the manager to the death position.",
      "The p0 trail cursor starts at the post-step point to keep Avatar.update from adding a normal trail point before the wall death."
    ]
  },
